<br>
Dark Tendrils: Make it useful at 50 Dual Wield by adding a debuff proc, not unlike the Valewalker styles... Dex/Qui or just Qui so our duel wield speed would really eat them up... I also have another idea for Tendrils, I'll get to that at the bottom...<br>
<br>
Flank/Shadows Rain: Flank needs some kind of To-Hit bonus, any kind... Even Low would be helpful... And this may be asking for too much, but as mentioned above, a small stun on Flank would stop those hit with it long enough to get Shadows Rain off...<br>
<br>
Penumbra/Misty Gloom: Could very well be a decent anytime chain in the Dual Wield repetior, the idea has lots of potential...<br>
<br>
Dark Tendrils (Revision): The one thing that still bothers me, is that Reflection/Hypnotic Darkness is still an enticing parry chain, having to choose between the Dark Tendrils (With Proc) or the Hypnotic Darkness chain with a nice stun would be extremely tough and there just isn't enough room on our Hotbars for both... Expecially for the Thrust Merc's (Like myself) who has a 3 hit evade chain taking up a nice slice of it... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.darkhosts.com/demised/chainwall.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=demised>Demised</A> at: 6/27/03 8:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=k8tpitta>k8tpitta</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary TL</span><br>  Posts: 428<br> <font color=#000000>(6/28/03 10:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blargle.com/boardstuff/fuu3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specific Feedback: Flank/DS/DT Changes</span><hr size=1> Ok,<br>
